<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-06 00:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Avalanche 4, Flames 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    DENVER (AP) -- Adam Deadmarsh scored three goals, Peter Forsberg had three
assists and rookie Marc Denis recorded his second career shutout, leading the
Colorado Avalanche past the Calgary Flames 4-0 Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
	   It was Deadmarsh's first career hat trick in 380 NHL games.
</P>
<P>
	   The Avalanche, maintaining their slim lead over Edmonton and Calgary in the
Northwest Division, got 27 saves from Denis, who recorded his fifth victory of
the season and third over the Flames.
</P>
<P>
	   Denis' most spectacular stop came in the final period, when his sweeping
glove save robbed Jarome Iginla of an apparent open-net goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Calgary's Fred Brathwaite had 30 saves.
</P>
<P>
	   Joe Sakic added a goal and an assist for Colorado.
</P>
<P>
	   Each team had only a single good scoring chance in a defensive and scoreless
first period, which saw Calgary outshoot Colorado 11-7. Calgary's Andrei Nazarov
and Colorado's Chris Dingman were assessed five-minute fighting penalties early
in the period.
</P>
<P>
	   Deadmarsh broke the scoring drought at 4:27 of the second. Forsberg took a
shot from just inside the right circle and Deadmarsh, stationed in front of the
goal, deflected the puck with his knee past Brathwaite.
</P>
<P>
	   Then, just 14 seconds after former Colorado wing Rene Corbet went off for
high-sticking, Sandis Ozolinsh hit Deadmarsh in stride behind defenseman Bobby
Dollas at the blue line, and Deadmarsh scored from the left circle at 17:33.
</P>
<P>
	   Colorado outshot Calgary 16-6 in the period.
</P>
<P>
	   Sakic made it 3-0 at 3:08 of the third. Martin Skoula carried the puck
behind the net and sent a pass in the right circle to Forsberg, who then found
an open Sakic left of the goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Forsberg's steal started a sequence that led to Deadmarsh's third goal and
11th of the season, from the right circle, at 16:39.
</P>
<P>
	   Calgary got off only two shots on its three power-play opportunities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-01-06-00 0003 </TRAILER>
