<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sharks 1, Oilers 1, Tie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    EDMONTON, Alberta (AP) -- Tommy Salo made 32 saves Wednesday night to help
the Edmonton Oilers to a 1-1 tie with the San Jose Sharks.
</P>
<P>
	   The Oilers led 1-0 on a second-period goal by Bill Guerin before Alexander
Korolyuk tied it for San Jose early in the third.
</P>
<P>
	   Doug Weight extended his point-scoring streak to five games with a perfect
pass that set up Guerin's 11th goal. Guerin's quick release from the slot beat
goalie Steve Shields high on the glove side at 19:12 of the second. Weight has
three goals and six assists during the streak.
</P>
<P>
	   Korolyuk knocked in a rebound of a shot by Patrick Marleau at 5:37 of the
third. The puck was sitting in the crease as Korolyuk swept it in from the side
to beat Salo.
</P>
<P>
	   Edmonton is undefeated in its past seven home games (4-0-3).
</P>
<P>
	   The Sharks outshot the Oilers 23-9 over the final 45 minutes and 33-21
overall.
</P>
<P>
	   Rem Murray returned to the Edmonton lineup after missing 28 games with
sprained ligaments in his right knee. To make room for Murray on the roster,
Michel Picard was placed on waivers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
