<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lightning 3, Canucks 3, Tie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) -- Pavel Kubina had a goal and an assist as
the Tampa Bay Lightning ended a seven-game losing streak Wednesday night with a
3-3 tie against the Vancouver Canucks.
</P>
<P>
	   Vancouver's Markus Naslund foiled the Lightning's victory bid, scoring with
9:50 left in the third period.
</P>
<P>
	   Ed Jovanovski made a game-saving play with 70 seconds left in overtime,
diving to poke the puck off away from Vincent Lecavalier, just as the
Lightning's second-leading scorer was coming in on a breakaway.
</P>
<P>
	   The Canucks (12-18-8) have gone 1-9-2 in their last 12 games. The Lightning
(10-21-6) are 0-7-2 since beating Carolina on Dec. 10, and 0-6-3 in their last
nine road games
</P>
<P>
	   Bryan Muir and Fredrick Modin also scored and Mike Sillinger set up a pair
for the Lightning, who earned their first point in seven visits to Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
	   Tampa Bay goalie Dan Cloutier stopped 35 shots, enjoying his best
performance in almost a month after giving up 23 goals in his last five starts,
all losses.
</P>
<P>
	   Alexander Mogilny and Peter Schaefer scored 32 seconds apart to give the
Canucks a brief 2-1 lead in the second period. Vancouver managed more than two
regulation goals for only the second time in 17 games.
</P>
<P>
	   Twisting and turning to elude two Tampa Bay defenders, Naslund scored his
team-leading 13th goal by snapping a 25-foot shot through a crowd, beating
Cloutier to tie it at 3.
</P>
<P>
	   Naslund's goal came five minutes after Muir scored a weak goal, beating
Felix Potvin through the legs with a shot from just inside the Canucks blue
line.
</P>
<P>
	   The Canucks, whose power-play is ranked 24th in the league, went 0-for-8
with the man advantage, including a 73-second two-man-advantage midway through
the second period.
</P>
<P>
	   The Lightning ran into injury troubles, losing two players. Forward Stan
Drulia did not return after sustaining a concussion when checked heavily into
the boards two minutes into the game.
</P>
<P>
	   Veteran defenseman Petr Svoboda was forced to leave in the second with a
shoulder injury.
</P>
<P>
	   Tampa Bay also played without Darcy Tucker, who served the second game of a
two-game suspension for spearing Florida's Todd Simpson on Dec. 27.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-01-06-00 0139 </TRAILER>
