the woman killed in the fiery limousine crash.
</P>
<P>
	   The white Lincoln Town Car went out of control, crashed through the
guardrail, flipped over and exploded in flames.
</P>
<P>
	   The limo's driver, seriously injured in the crash, hasn't been able to give
police many details and does not know the passenger's name, police said.
</P>
<P>
	   The woman's body, charred beyond recognition, remained at the medical
examiner's office in Farmington.
</P>
<P>
	   "Someone must have seen something," said Master Sgt. Patrick O'Hara of Troop
F in Westbrook.
</P>
<P>
	   The accident occurred between 8:30 and 9:15 p.m., between exits 70 and 71.
O'Hara said no drivers stopped to offer assistance.
</P>
<P>
	   The driver, Ik H. Kim, 44, of Syosset, N.Y., managed to escape. He was
listed in serious condition in the intensive care unit at Lawrence &AMP; Memorial
Hospital.
</P>
