<HEADLINE> Dow Steady; Nasdaq Falls 46  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are mixed in early trading. The Dow Jones
Industrial Average is little changed in today's early going, helped by some of
the financial stocks. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold an
eight-to-five lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 46 points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is down two points.
</P>
<P>
	   Analysts say market sentiment remains nervous in the wake of this week's
technology-led selloff. Global markets have weakened again heading into today's
session. There is also some nervousness ahead of the release tomorrow of
December employment data. True, this morning's weekly jobless claims report was
weaker than expected. But the Labor Department advises that the report released
this time of year tends to be volatile because of the holidays.
</P>
<P>
	   Computer maker Gateway did nothing to help tech investors get over their
case of the nerves, after revealing late yesterday that fourth-quarter earnings
will fall below expectations. It cited a Y2K-induced sales slowdown, coupled
with what it described as difficulty getting components from Intel.
</P>
<P>
	   Retail chains have reported their same-store sales figures. While Toys R Us
has reported lackluster results, jewelry seller Tiffany has delivered blowout
sales numbers.
