<HEADLINE> Kellogg Hires Ford Exec As CFO  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    BATTLE CREEK, Mich. (AP) -- Kellogg Corp. has hired Thomas J. Webb, a Ford
Motor Co. financial specialist, as its chief financial officer.
</P>
<P>
	   Webb becomes executive vice president of the cereal maker, which has
suffered flat cereal sales and a sliding market share. He was chief financial
information officer of Ford, where he worked for 22 years.
</P>
<P>
	   Kellogg's chief financial officer John R. Hinton and four other top
executives resigned in March.
</P>
<P>
	   "Tom Webb brings outstanding financial and analytical skills to Kellogg,"
said Kellogg president and chief executive Carlos M. Gutierrez. He said the
appointment completes the company's executive overhaul.
</P>
<P>
	   Long the biggest U.S. cereal maker, Kellogg fell behind Minnesota-based
General Mills in the four-week period ended Dec. 5.
</P>
<P>
	   Kellogg's market share was 27.9 percent, compared with 29.8 percent for
General Mills, according to supermarket data collected by Information Resources
Inc.
</P>
<P>
	   In the last two years, Kellogg has cut hundreds of jobs worldwide to save
money.
</P>
<P>
	   In November, it closed the oldest part of its historic hometown cereal plant
in Battle Creek.
</P>
<P>
	   Kellogg has said it will debut at least five new cereals in 2000, along with
promotions featuring supermodel Cindy Crawford and basketball star Grant Hill.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-01-06-00 1223 </TRAILER>
