<HEADLINE> Northland Selling Juice Business  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    WISCONSIN RAPIDS, Wis. (AP) -- Northland Cranberries Inc. has agreed to sell
its private label juice business, which makes cranberry blends under supermarket
store brand names.
</P>
<P>
	   The business is being sold to Cliffstar Corp. of Dunkirk, N.Y., for $32
million to $36 million, Northland chairman and chief executive John Swendrowski
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The final price of the sale will depend on the value of inventory when the
sale closes at the end of February, he said.
</P>
<P>
	   Northland's private label business accounts for about $43 million of the
company's $237 million in annual revenue.
</P>
<P>
	   Northland's flagship products are its pure juice blends.
</P>
<P>
	   "This sale will allow us to focus entirely on building the Northland and
Seneca brands within the juice category," Swendrowski said.
</P>
<P>
	   Ocean Spray, a growers' cooperative based in Lakeville-Middleboro, Mass.,
holds about half of the U.S. cranberry juice market, compared to 12.6 percent
for Northland, based in Wisconsin Rapids.
</P>
</TEXT>
