<HEADLINE> Armenian TV Official Detained  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) -- A top Armenian national television executive has
been detained in the fatal attack on parliament last fall, officials said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   There were no immediate details about the detention of Arutun Arutunian. The
Military Prosecutor's Office will seek a formal arrest within 96 hours, the
Interfax news agency said.
</P>
<P>
	   In Armenia, suspects can be held for that period without being charged.
Arutunian is deputy director of Armenian national television.
</P>
<P>
	   In the Oct. 27 attack, gunmen burst into the parliament chamber during a
session and opened fire, killing Prime Minister Vazgen Sarkisian, the parliament
speaker and six others.
</P>
<P>
	   The gunmen took some 40 legislators hostage and held them overnight before
surrendering.
</P>
