	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Technology stocks fell for a third straight
session today as investors shifted money from the pricey shares
that dominated trading in 1999 to blue-chip stalwarts like
Caterpillar, 3M and Procter &AMP; Gamble. The Dow Jones industrial
average rose 130.61 to 11,253.26. The Nasdaq composite index,
dominated by technology stocks, fell 150.34 to 3,727.20. It was the
