	   Microsoft, Barnes &AMP; Noble Make Deal
</P>
<P>
	   SEATTLE (AP) -- Microsoft Corp. and Barnes &AMP; Noble Inc. plan to
develop and market electronic books using Microsoft's new
``ClearType'' technology. Barnes &AMP; Noble's bookstores, along with
the barnesandnoble.com Web site, will begin offering e-books
starting in the middle of this year, according to Barnes &AMP; Noble
vice chairman Steve Riggio. By that time, Microsoft will have
included its Microsoft Reader software, under development for more
than a year, in most of its operating systems, including systems
that run WebTV and a new series of palm-size computing devices due
out in the next several months.
</P>
