</P>
<P>
	   BATTLE CREEK, Mich. (AP) -- Kellogg Corp. has hired Thomas J.
Webb, a Ford Motor Co. financial specialist, as its chief financial
officer. Webb becomes executive vice president of the cereal maker,
which has suffered flat cereal sales and a sliding market share. He
was chief financial information officer of Ford, where he worked
for 22 years. Kellogg's chief financial officer John R. Hinton and
four other top executives resigned in March. Long the biggest U.S.
cereal maker, Kellogg fell behind Minnesota-based General Mills in
the four-week period ended Dec. 5.
</P>
<P>
