</P>
<P>
	   ROUSEVILLE, Pa. (AP) -- Pennzoil-Quaker State Co. plans to close
its refinery and packaging plant in northwestern Pennsylvania that
employs about 300 people and is trying to sell its refinery in
Shreveport, La. The company said today it would charge $293 million
against after-tax earnings because of closing the plant in
Rouseville and for a writedown in the value of the Shreveport
refinery. The Rouseville refinery processes Penn Grade Crude oil
and ships it to other oil companies. The nearby packaging plant
prepares Pennzoil and Wolf's Head oils for market.
</P>
