<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Money Funds Up by $15.96B  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Assets of the nation's retail money market mutual funds
rose by $15.96 billion in the latest week to $949.15 billion, the Investment
Company Institute said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   Assets of taxable money market funds in the retail category rose by $11.52
billion to $787.75 billion for the week ended Wednesday, the Washington-based
mutual fund trade group said. Tax-exempt fund assets rose by $4.44 billion to
$161.40 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   Assets of institutional money market funds fell by $3.75 billion to $688.52
billion for the same period. Among institutional funds, taxable money market
fund assets fell by $6.42 billion to $636.95 billion; assets of tax-exempt funds
rose by $2.67 billion to $51.56 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   Total money market assets stood at $1.638 trillion for the week.
</P>
<P>
	   Assets for the previous week were revised to $1.625 trillion to reflect
reporting errors and a change in the number of funds reporting.
</P>
<P>
	   The seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds ell in the week
ended Tuesday to 4.90 percent from 5.13 percent the previous week, said IBC's
Money Fund Report, a trade journal published in Ashland, Mass., by IBC Financial
Data Inc. The 30-day average yield fell to 5.05 percent from 5.08 percent, IBC
Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
	   The seven-day compounded yield fell to 5.02 percent from 5.26 percent the
previous week, and the 30-day compounded yield fell to 5.18 percent from 5.21
percent, IBC Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
	   The average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 46 days, down
from 48 days, IBC Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
	   The online service bankrate.com said its survey of 100 leading commercial
banks, savings and loan associations and savings banks in the nation's 10
largest markets showed the annual percentage yield available on money market
accounts as of Wednesday was unchanged at 2.07 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   The North Palm Beach, Fla.-based unit of Intelligent Life Corp. said the
annual percentage yield available on interest-bearing checking accounts rose to
0.85 percent from 0.84 percent a week earlier.
</P>
<P>
	   Bankrate.com said the annual percentage yield was 4.63 percent on six-month
certificates of deposit, down from 4.66 percent the previous week. Yields were
5.01 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 4.99 percent; 5.23 percent on 2 1/2-year
CDs, up from 5.20 percent; and 5.54 percent on 5-year CDs, up from 5.50 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
