<HEADLINE> McCain Defends His Musical Tastes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- After a day spent defending his ethics, Sen. John McCain
wasn't expecting an attack on his taste in music.
</P>
<P>
	   During the Republican presidential debate Thursday night in Durham, N.H.,
former U.N. Ambassador Alan Keyes brought up recent comments by McCain on
television that his favorite rock group was Nine Inch Nails. Keyes said the TV
program then displayed some of the group's lyrics, which were laced with
profanities.
</P>
<P>
