<P>
	   McCain responded like a contestant on ``Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?''
</P>
<P>
	   ``Can I get a lifeline?'' the Arizona senator quipped. He said he wanted to
confer with his 15-year-old daughter, who recently accompanied him to the MTV
Video Music Awards.
</P>
<P>
	   McCain first said humor was important in politics, but then grew serious.
</P>
<P>
	   ``I agree with you that they're being subjected to terrible influences,''
McCain said. ``Yes, I was trying to be amusing and entertaining, and it was a
poor choice.''
</P>
<P>
	   Keyes agreed. ``I'm a father and I'm not laughing, I'm really not.''
