<HEADLINE> LA Councilman Pleads Innocent  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A former sheriff's sergeant who now serves on the
Palmdale city council pleaded innocent Thursday to numerous counts of child
molestation.
</P>
<P>
	   Kevin Carney turned himself in a day after he was charged with 17 felony
counts of child molestation involving four girls, and one misdemeanor charge of
possessing child pornography.
</P>
<P>
	   Carney was jailed on $2 million bond. He faces life in prison if convicted.
</P>
<P>
	   His attorney, Milton Grimes, said Thursday there was nothing to the charges
involving the girls. Carney declined to comment to reporters at the hearing.
</P>
<P>
	   Voters in Palmdale, about 50 miles north of Los Angeles, elected Carney to
the council in November, shortly after he was arrested for investigation of lewd
conduct with a 14-year-old girl.
</P>
<P>
	   He denied the charges, calling them part of a dirty smear campaign from his
opponent, and was freed on bail.
</P>
<P>
	   Carney, a 23-year sheriff's department veteran, retired a month after his
arrest in October. At one time, he was a leading sex abuse investigator,
supervising cases involving children.
</P>
<P>
	   He was removed from that detail in 1997 after being accused of
inappropriately touching two 9-year-olds. While charges were not filed at the
time, six of the counts filed Wednesday involve that case.
</P>
</TEXT>
