<HEADLINE> Amtrak Train Derails in Montana  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ESSEX, Mont. (AP) -- A locomotive and four cars of a Seattle-to-Chicago
Amtrak train derailed Thursday as the train prepared to stop at this
northwestern Montana settlement. No one was injured.
</P>
<P>
	   About 200 passengers remained aboard the idle train hours after the
derailment, but were later taken to a local inn. The train, which derailed at
9:05 a.m., was still stationary 12 hours later.
</P>
<P>
	   Amtrak spokesman Kevin Johnson described the derailment of the Empire
Builder train as minor.
</P>
<P>
	   There had been plans to transport the passengers aboard cars that remained
on the tracks, but that plan was delayed because of the time necessary for
Burlington Northern Santa Fe to investigate the derailment, Johnson said.
</P>
<P>
	   ``BNSF is investigating it and they won't let us go until they're done,'' he
said. ``If it goes on much longer, we may have to make alternate transportation
plans for our riders. But that call hasn't been made yet.''
</P>
<P>
	   The derailed cars included the diner, a baggage car, a crew sleeper and a
passenger sleeper, Johnson said. The train consisted of three locomotives and 11
cars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
